## **Indexing columns in SQL to improve query performance**  

**1. Single-Column Index:**  

```CREATE INDEX idx_column_name ON table_name (column_name);``` 
This creates an index on a single column. It is effective when filtering, joining, or ordering based on that column.  

**2. Composite Index:**  

CREATE INDEX idx_column1_column2 ON table_name (column1, column2);  
Composite indexes involve multiple columns. They are beneficial when queries involve filtering, joining, or ordering using a combination of those columns.  

**3. Unique Index:**  

CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_column_name ON table_name (column_name);  
A unique index ensures the uniqueness of values in the indexed column(s).  
It improves query performance when enforcing uniqueness or when performing lookups using the indexed column.
